bug.short_desc: [abrt] atril: gtk_widget_get_parent(): atril killed by SIGSEGV

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: I downloaded a pdf from a website and I viewed it. I closed the pdf, did a few little things for a couple of minutes, then hit the down arrow in Firefox for recent downloads. I clicked the pdf there to view it again and this is when the pdf viewer crashed.
Version-Release number of selected component: atril-1.12.2-1.fc24
Additional info: reporter: libreport-2.6.3 backtrace_rating: 4 cmdline: atril /tmp/mozilla_pgervase0/statement.pdf crash_function: gtk_widget_get_parent executable: /usr/bin/atril global_pid: 25362 kernel: 4.5.0-0.rc0.git1.1.fc24.x86_64 runlevel: N 5 type: CCpp uid: 1000
Truncated backtrace: Thread no. 1 (10 frames) #0 gtk_widget_get_parent at gtkwidget.c:6483 #1 ev_window_set_document at ev-window.c:1583 #2 ev_window_document_changed_cb at ev-window.c:4858 #8 g_object_notify_by_spec_internal at gobject.c:1155 #9 g_object_notify at gobject.c:1203 #10 ev_document_model_set_document at ev-document-model.c:306 #11 ev_window_reload_job_cb at ev-window.c:1832 #12 _g_closure_invoke_va at gclosure.c:867 #15 emit_finished at ev-jobs.c:193 #20 gtk_main at gtkmain.c:1268
Potential duplicate: bug 1164560
